<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910320-0141</DOCNO><DOCID>910320-0141.</DOCID><HL>   Dynamics Corp. to Sell Unit</HL><DATE>03/20/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A8</SO><CO>   DYA</CO><IN>TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)POLLUTION CONTROL, WASTE MANAGEMENT SERVICES (POL)INDUSTRIAL AND COMMERCIAL SERVICES (SVC)</IN><LP>   GREENWICH, Conn. -- Dynamics Corp. of America said itsigned a letter of intent to sell its Anemostat Productsdivision to Halton OY of Kausala, Finland, for $14 million.   The unit makes air-distribution equipment forenvironmental control of laboratories and buildings, and foraircraft, rail and marine equipment. Its 1990 sales totaled$22.9 million.</LP><TEXT>   Halton is the parent of a group of Europeanair-distribution equipment makers, with 1990 sales of $90million.   Dynamics Corp. businesses include electronic parts, mobilevans and transportable shelters, portable electric housewaresand appliances.</TEXT></DOC>